%% Sequence — warm turn with SSE redact (Phase 2)
%% Shows the new redact() pass on the SSE body. Phase 4 routing is implicit
%% (drawer is on the HTTP SSE path, no WS bridge).

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Operator
    participant Drawer as CopilotDrawer.svelte
    participant Routes as drive_native_sse
    participant Stream as ReaderStream pipe
    participant Redact as sse_handler::redact()
    participant Memory as HelixSessionMemory
    participant Provider as OllamaCliProvider
    participant Cloud as Ollama Cloud

    Note over Drawer: Phase 4: native agents use HTTP SSE,<br/>no WS bridge, no pendingMessages queue
    Operator->>Drawer: types follow-up + Enter
    Drawer->>Routes: POST /api/builds/:id/copilot (session continues)
    Routes->>Memory: load_turns(build_id)
    Memory-->>Routes: conversation_history (replayed verbatim)
    Routes->>Provider: spawn_streaming(SanitizedAgentRequest{messages, system, tools})
    Provider->>Cloud: POST /v1/messages
    Cloud-->>Provider: SSE stream
    Provider-->>Stream: ProviderEvent::Text(chunk)
    Note over Stream,Redact: Phase 2: every chunk passes through redact()<br/>against session_token + la_native_api_key<br/>before crossing the SSE wire to the client
    Stream->>Redact: redact(chunk, token, api_key)
    Redact-->>Stream: clean chunk (or [REDACTED] markers)
    Stream-->>Drawer: event: text {"chunk":"clean"}
    Provider-->>Stream: ProviderEvent::Complete
    Stream-->>Drawer: event: complete
    Drawer-->>Operator: append assistant bubble; hide Thinking…
    Drawer->>Memory: persist turn (assistant role)
